               <p>CALVERT BOWYER VAUX. I am a <rs id="t18311020-27-viclabel152" type="occupation">surgeon</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311020-27-victim292 t18311020-27-viclabel152"></join>. On the 7th of October I was in <placeName id="t18311020-27-crimeloc153">Laurence Pountney-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311020-27-crimeloc153" type="placeName" value="Laurence Pountney-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311020-27-crimeloc153" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311020-27-off150 t18311020-27-crimeloc153"></join>, about twelve o'clock, and had a snuff-box in my coat pocket; I felt a twitch, turned round, and saw the prisoner and another shuffling my box between them - I saw it distinctly in the prisoner's hand; they were just across the lane, about ten yards from me - the prisoner ran away, the other remained; I followed the prisoner, calling Stop thief! down Cannon-street and Laurence Pountney-hill - the street-keeper joined in the pursuit, and opposite Suffolk-lane I saw the prisoner throw the box out of his hand- I took it up; the street-keeper followed, and very shortly brought him to me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you see me take it? A. I felt my pocket move, and saw it in your hand.</p>
               <p>
            
